50|$|The {{disparity}} {{of costs}} to the project's various constituents has been a frequent source of controversy. Although the overall average cost of SWP water is $147 per <b>acre-foot</b> ($119 per 1,000 m3), agricultural users pay far less than their urban counterparts for SWP water. The Kern County Water Agency (the second largest SWP entitlement holder) pays around $45-50 per <b>acre-foot</b> ($36-41 per 1,000 m3) of SWP water, which is mostly used for irrigation. The Metropolitan Water District of Southern California (the largest entitlement holder) pays $298 per <b>acre-foot</b> ($241 per 1,000 m3). This basically means that cities are subsidizing the cost of farm water, even though the cities also provided primary funding {{for the construction of}} the SWP.|$|E
